"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-07-11-first-time-olympians-carry-legacy\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Jamaica Athletics Administrative Association (JAAA) President Garth Gayle and Olympic gold medallist Donald Quarrie have both hailed the selection of at least 36 first-time members of the Jamaican track and field team to the Paris Olympic Games as a sign of continued development in the sport.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 293, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 44, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica_Athletics_Administrative_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jamaica Athletics Administrative Association\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica_Athletics_Administrative_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica_Athletics_Administrative_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 68, \"end\": 73, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Gayle\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.104212230215389e-20, \"text\": \"Gayle\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Gayle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Gayle\"}, {\"begin\": 101, \"end\": 115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Don_Quarrie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Donald Quarrie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Don_Quarrie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Don_Quarrie\"}, {\"begin\": 188, \"end\": 196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9938445800726005, \"rank\": 0.00619354379045981, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic gold medallist\", \"from\": 78, \"to\": 100}, {\"ngram\": \"the selection\", \"from\": 133, \"to\": 146}, {\"ngram\": \"at least 36 first-time members\", \"from\": 150, \"to\": 180}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympic Games\", \"from\": 221, \"to\": 244}, {\"ngram\": \"a sign\", \"from\": 248, \"to\": 254}, {\"ngram\": \"continued development\", \"from\": 258, \"to\": 279}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 283, \"to\": 292}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 36 athletes represent just over half of the track and field team that was released earlier this week and sees a good blend of youth and experience.\", \"from\": 295, \"to\": 446, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 36 athletes\", \"from\": 295, \"to\": 310}, {\"ngram\": \"just over half\", \"from\": 321, \"to\": 335}, {\"ngram\": \"the track and field team\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 363}, {\"ngram\": \"a good blend\", \"from\": 409, \"to\": 421}, {\"ngram\": \"youth\", \"from\": 425, \"to\": 430}, {\"ngram\": \"experience\", \"from\": 435, \"to\": 445}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is what development is all about, the juniors being able to hold their own against the seniors,\\\" Gayle told theJamaica Observer.\", \"from\": 448, \"to\": 582, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 551, \"end\": 556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Gayle\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.104212230215389e-20, \"text\": \"Gayle\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Gayle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Gayle\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"what development\", \"from\": 457, \"to\": 473}, {\"ngram\": \"the juniors\", \"from\": 488, \"to\": 499}, {\"ngram\": \"the seniors\", \"from\": 537, \"to\": 548}, {\"ngram\": \"theJamaica Observer\", \"from\": 562, \"to\": 581}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's not just in the sprints but jumps and throws, continued developments across the board and we are very pleased.\\\"\", \"from\": 584, \"to\": 701, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the sprints\", \"from\": 602, \"to\": 613}, {\"ngram\": \"continued developments\", \"from\": 636, \"to\": 658}, {\"ngram\": \"the board\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 675}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Quarrie, who will be part of the Jamaica Olympic Association's delegation and will be working with the athletics team, described the numbers as \\\"wonderful\\\".\", \"from\": 703, \"to\": 859, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 736, \"end\": 763, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica_Olympic_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jamaica Olympic Association\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica_Olympic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica_Olympic_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Quarrie\", \"from\": 703, \"to\": 710}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 728}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletics team\", \"from\": 802, \"to\": 820}, {\"ngram\": \"the numbers\", \"from\": 832, \"to\": 843}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We do not need to go back to any rebuilding phase,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 861, \"to\": 922, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any rebuilding phase\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 911}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have the talent to take us through any transition period.\\\"\", \"from\": 923, \"to\": 985, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the talent\", \"from\": 932, \"to\": 942}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 951, \"to\": 953}, {\"ngram\": \"any transition period\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 983}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gayle told theObserver, \\\"We have been seeing the continued rise of the juniors coming through the system, those who competed at the Boys' and Girls' Champions, the Carifta Games, and the World Athletics Under-20 Games as well and are now running side by side with the seniors.\\\"\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 1264, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1174, \"end\": 1189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.999992977818337, \"rank\": 7.022231111647882e-06, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gayle\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 992}, {\"ngram\": \"theObserver\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1009}, {\"ngram\": \"the continued rise\", \"from\": 1032, \"to\": 1050}, {\"ngram\": \"the juniors\", \"from\": 1054, \"to\": 1065}, {\"ngram\": \"the system\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1091}, {\"ngram\": \"the Boys\", \"from\": 1115, \"to\": 1123}, {\"ngram\": \"Girls' Champions\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1145}, {\"ngram\": \"the Carifta Games\", \"from\": 1147, \"to\": 1164}, {\"ngram\": \"side\", \"from\": 1241, \"to\": 1245}, {\"ngram\": \"the seniors\", \"from\": 1251, \"to\": 1262}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gayle says that the structure was put in place to see the younger athletes excel from the first step.\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1367, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1266, \"end\": 1271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Gayle\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.104212230215389e-20, \"text\": \"Gayle\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Gayle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Gayle\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the structure\", \"from\": 1282, \"to\": 1295}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1312}, {\"ngram\": \"the younger athletes\", \"from\": 1320, \"to\": 1340}, {\"ngram\": \"the first step\", \"from\": 1352, \"to\": 1366}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are grateful for the work done by local-based coaches and even those at the high schools level as it is a vital aspect of our development,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1521, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the work\", \"from\": 1390, \"to\": 1398}, {\"ngram\": \"local-based coaches\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1426}, {\"ngram\": \"even those\", \"from\": 1431, \"to\": 1441}, {\"ngram\": \"the high schools level\", \"from\": 1445, \"to\": 1467}, {\"ngram\": \"a vital aspect\", \"from\": 1477, \"to\": 1491}, {\"ngram\": \"our development\", \"from\": 1495, \"to\": 1510}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Jamaica has a rich tradition in track and field and might I say, it will continue for quite some time.\\\"\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1626, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1523, \"end\": 1530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1840745533174118e-18, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a rich tradition\", \"from\": 1535, \"to\": 1551}, {\"ngram\": \"track\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1560}, {\"ngram\": \"field\", \"from\": 1565, \"to\": 1570}, {\"ngram\": \"quite some time\", \"from\": 1609, \"to\": 1624}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gayle said the development was not only on the track or in the field.\", \"from\": 1628, \"to\": 1697, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gayle\", \"from\": 1628, \"to\": 1633}, {\"ngram\": \"the development\", \"from\": 1639, \"to\": 1654}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 1671, \"to\": 1680}, {\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1696}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's not just the coaches, but our administrators, school principals, high school alumnus, all these groups play their part and they do serve a vital role in the continued development of Jamaica's track and field and we are looking forward to an excellent Paris Olympics.\\\"\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1972, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1887, \"end\": 1894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1840745533174118e-18, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 1956, \"end\": 1970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"just the coaches\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1725}, {\"ngram\": \"school principals\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 1768}, {\"ngram\": \"high school alumnus\", \"from\": 1770, \"to\": 1789}, {\"ngram\": \"all these groups\", \"from\": 1791, \"to\": 1807}, {\"ngram\": \"their part\", \"from\": 1813, \"to\": 1823}, {\"ngram\": \"a vital role\", \"from\": 1842, \"to\": 1854}, {\"ngram\": \"the continued development\", \"from\": 1858, \"to\": 1883}, {\"ngram\": \"field\", \"from\": 1907, \"to\": 1912}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the first-time Olympians are athletes who have starred at the junior level are Jaydon Hibbert and Roshawn Clarke, who both broke World Under-20 records last year, and were medallists at the last two stagings of the World Under-20 Championships in Nairobi, Kenya, in 2021 and the next year, 2022, in Cali, Colombia.\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 2294, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2066, \"end\": 2073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toots_Hibbert\", \"score\": 0.9999999973761078, \"rank\": 2.6239043805652924e-09, \"text\": \"Hibbert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toots_Hibbert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toots_Hibbert\"}, {\"begin\": 2195, \"end\": 2223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2018_IAAF_World_U20_Championships\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1951581873031024e-19, \"text\": \"World Under-20 Championships\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2018_IAAF_World_U20_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2018_IAAF_World_U20_Championships\"}, {\"begin\": 2227, \"end\": 2234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nairobi\", \"score\": 0.9999999732858672, \"rank\": 2.3935834665365156e-08, \"text\": \"Nairobi\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nairobi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nairobi\"}, {\"begin\": 2236, \"end\": 2241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9886751732506069, \"rank\": 0.011442234511944089, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya_national_cricket_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2279, \"end\": 2283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cali\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.524397431929626e-12, \"text\": \"Cali\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cali\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first-time Olympians\", \"from\": 1980, \"to\": 2004}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2009, \"to\": 2017}, {\"ngram\": \"the junior level\", \"from\": 2038, \"to\": 2054}, {\"ngram\": \"World Under-20 records\", \"from\": 2109, \"to\": 2131}, {\"ngram\": \"medallists\", \"from\": 2152, \"to\": 2162}, {\"ngram\": \"the last two stagings\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2187}, {\"ngram\": \"the next year\", \"from\": 2255, \"to\": 2268}, {\"ngram\": \"Colombia\", \"from\": 2285, \"to\": 2293}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Newly minted 100m hurdles national record holder Ackera Nugent was a gold medallist in Nairobi, where 100m qualifier Tia Clayton was a gold medallist on the women's 4x100m team.\", \"from\": 2296, \"to\": 2473, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2345, \"end\": 2358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ackera_Nugent\", \"score\": 0.9999999994784048, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ackera Nugent\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ackera_Nugent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ackera_Nugent\"}, {\"begin\": 2383, \"end\": 2390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nairobi\", \"score\": 0.9999999732858672, \"rank\": 2.3935834665365156e-08, \"text\": \"Nairobi\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nairobi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nairobi\"}, {\"begin\": 2413, \"end\": 2424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tia_Clayton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tia Clayton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tia_Clayton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tia_Clayton\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"100m hurdles national record holder\", \"from\": 2309, \"to\": 2344}, {\"ngram\": \"a gold medallist\", \"from\": 2363, \"to\": 2379}, {\"ngram\": \"a gold medallist\", \"from\": 2429, \"to\": 2445}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's 4x100m team\", \"from\": 2449, \"to\": 2472}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ackelia Smith, a finalist in the women's triple jump, men's 200m champion Bryan Levell and Ralford Mullings, the 2021 men's discus throw silver medallist, are also part of the team.\", \"from\": 2475, \"to\": 2656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2549, \"end\": 2554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Bryan\", \"score\": 0.5837191881118795, \"rank\": 0.7131173279205553, \"text\": \"Bryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Bryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Bryan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ackelia Smith\", \"from\": 2475, \"to\": 2488}, {\"ngram\": \"a finalist\", \"from\": 2490, \"to\": 2500}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's triple jump\", \"from\": 2504, \"to\": 2527}, {\"ngram\": \"men's 200m champion\", \"from\": 2529, \"to\": 2548}, {\"ngram\": \"Ralford Mullings\", \"from\": 2566, \"to\": 2582}, {\"ngram\": \"silver medallist\", \"from\": 2612, \"to\": 2628}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 2639, \"to\": 2643}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 2647, \"to\": 2655}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Quarrie said he is looking forward to meeting the team members as soon as possible, especially the first-timers and said their success would also motivate the next set of athletes - those in high school and the college system.\", \"from\": 2658, \"to\": 2884, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Quarrie\", \"from\": 2658, \"to\": 2665}, {\"ngram\": \"the team members\", \"from\": 2704, \"to\": 2720}, {\"ngram\": \"their success\", \"from\": 2779, \"to\": 2792}, {\"ngram\": \"the next set\", \"from\": 2813, \"to\": 2825}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2829, \"to\": 2837}, {\"ngram\": \"high school\", \"from\": 2849, \"to\": 2860}, {\"ngram\": \"the college system\", \"from\": 2865, \"to\": 2883}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He hopes as many of the first-timers would be able to participate in the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 2885, \"to\": 2975, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first-timers\", \"from\": 2905, \"to\": 2921}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2954, \"to\": 2974}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is one of the big traditions of the Olympic Games and it is great for the athletes to be part of it and you get a real feel of the Olympic spirit,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2977, \"to\": 3139, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the big traditions\", \"from\": 2993, \"to\": 3011}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 3015, \"to\": 3032}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 3053, \"to\": 3065}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 3072, \"to\": 3076}, {\"ngram\": \"a real feel\", \"from\": 3095, \"to\": 3106}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic spirit\", \"from\": 3110, \"to\": 3128}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Quarrie said the future is bright for some of the young Jamaicans.\", \"from\": 3141, \"to\": 3207, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3197, \"end\": 3206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J